# CLAUDE.md — Claude Code adapter for Solon Product SFS (entry-lean)

This project uses Solon Product SFS, the **Solo Founder System** for AI-native product work
(multi-adaptor by design — Claude Code / Codex / Gemini CLI 동등 1급).

## Entry (token-min)

- Continue from the smallest durable entrypoint: `/sfs status` → current sprint `report.md`.
- Do not auto-load verbose history (`events.jsonl`, old `scheduled_task_log`, old `review-runs`) unless needed.

Resume hints (default order):
- `/sfs status` (1-line dashboard)
- `.sfs-local/current-sprint` → `.sfs-local/sprints/<id>/report.md`
- If blocked: `.sfs-local/sprints/<id>/retro.md`, then relevant ADRs under `.sfs-local/decisions/`

## Agent/model setting guard

When the user asks about agent/model settings, inspect `.sfs-local/model-profiles.yaml` first.
If it is missing or unconfirmed (`selected_runtime: current` / `selected_policy: current_model`),
do not claim it is configured. Say it is a current-model fallback and ask which policy to apply.

## SFS commands — deterministic bash adapter SSoT

Solon SFS slash commands dispatch to the global `sfs <command>` runtime (deterministic bash adapter).

Rules:
- Always run the adapter first for `/sfs <command>` / `sfs <command>`.
- Print adapter `stdout` verbatim; on non-zero exit also show `stderr` + exit code (no paraphrase).
- If `sfs` is missing on PATH, say so in 1 line and point to install/upgrade.
- If `/sfs loop` indicates a mutex conflict (Solon `domain_locks`), stop and report the lock owner/domain.

Hybrid refinement (only when the adapter created/pointed to files):
- `brainstorm|plan|implement|decision|report|retro`: refine the created artifact(s) and answer as a Solon report.
- `review`: summarize/translate from recorded results; do not dump raw executor output unless asked.

Keep questions to 1–3 when critical info is missing; do not auto-run the next gate.

Full reference (only when needed):
- `.claude/commands/sfs.md` (slash help + usage)
- `sfs guide --print` (project onboarding guide)
